/*
This is a comment block. It won't be read as an Ink story.
Comments are very useful for leaving ideas for story and functionalty

This exercise will demonstrate the following in the example video:
 - Varrying text via loops
 - Functions
 
 In the assignment:
 - A story with at least 6 knots
 - Vary some text via a loop
* Create a function that serves as a timer. (This is shown in the video)
*/


VAR time = -1 //  0 Morning, 1 Noon, 2 Night


You are trying to look for some nice seashells to make you mom a necklace  -> seashore

== seashore ==
You are trying to look for some nice Seashells to make you mom a necklace.
You are on the beach. 

It is { advance_time()  }

+ [Stroll down the beach] -> beach2
-> DONE

== beach2 ==
This is further down the beach.

It is {advance_time() }

+ {time == 1} [Pick up some seashells] -> shells
+ {time == 2} [Pick up some seashells] -> Pretty_Shell


+ [Move back up the beach] -> seashore

== shells ==
You pick up the shells
-> beach2

=== Pretty_Shell ===
You see a very pretty Shell for your moms necklace

+ [Pick it up] -> Hermit_Crab 

=== Hermit_Crab ===
You go to pick up the shell and a little crab pops out!
Both you and the little crab are suprised.
You drop the crab but the crab Shares a look with you and you feel like you should follow it.

+ [Go back to looking for shells] -> seashore
* [ Follow the little crab] -> Perfect_Shells

=== Perfect_Shells ===
You trust your gut and follow the crab.
He leads you to a log and he stands next to it.
You think he wants you to look inside.

* [Look inside] -> End

=== End ===
Inside the log you see a large collection of beatiful shells!
These will make a wonderful necklace for your mother!
You thank your new friend and head home.

-> END


== function advance_time ==

    ~ time = time + 1
    
    {
        - time > 2:
            ~ time = 0
    }    
    
    {    
        - time == 0:
            ~ return "Morning"
        
        - time == 1:
            ~ return "Noon"
        
        - time == 2:
            ~ return "Night"
    
    }

    
        
    ~ return time
    
    
